  "text": "The complete chain from Deployment spec change to Pod creation in Kubernetes v1.32.0 involves three major components: the Deployment controller, the ReplicaSet controller, and the Pod creation in the API server.\n\n**Stage 1: Deployment Controller Reconciliation**\nWhen a Deployment spec changes (e.g., image update, replicas change), the Deployment controller's syncDeployment method (pkg/controller/deployment/deployment_controller.go:590) is invoked. This is the entry point for deployment reconciliation. The syncDeployment function determines the deployment strategy and routes to either rolloutRecreate or rolloutRolling.\n\nFor rolling updates, rolloutRolling (pkg/controller/deployment/rolling.go:31) is called. This method calls getAllReplicaSetsAndSyncRevision, which invokes getNewReplicaSet (pkg/controller/deployment/sync.go:138). The getNewReplicaSet method is the critical link that creates a new ReplicaSet when the deployment's pod template changes. At line 224 of sync.go, it calls:\n  dc.client.AppsV1().ReplicaSets(d.Namespace).Create(ctx, &newRS, metav1.CreateOptions{})\nThis creates a ReplicaSet object in the API server.\n\n**Stage 2: ReplicaSet Controller Reconciliation**\nOnce the ReplicaSet is created, the ReplicaSet controller detects it (via informer watches) and calls syncReplicaSet (pkg/controller/replicaset/replica_set.go:675). This is the entry point for replicaset reconciliation.\n\nsyncReplicaSet calls manageReplicas (pkg/controller/replicaset/replica_set.go:569) at line 722. This method is responsible for ensuring the desired number of pod replicas exist. When fewer pods than desired are running, it calls:\n  rsc.podControl.CreatePods(ctx, rs.Namespace, &rs.Spec.Template, rs, metav1.NewControllerRef(rs, rsc.GroupVersionKind))\nat line 598.\n\n**Stage 3: Pod Creation**\nThe podControl is an instance of RealPodControl (pkg/controller/controller_utils.go:473). The CreatePods method (pkg/controller/controller_utils.go:530) wraps CreatePodsWithGenerateName, which calls GetPodFromTemplate to construct the pod object and then calls createPods (pkg/controller/controller_utils.go:578).\n\nThe createPods method (line 578) is where the actual API call happens:\n  r.KubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n\n**Stage 4: Pod Persisted in API Server**\nThe API server receives the Pod creation request and routes it to the pod REST handler. The REST handler (pkg/registry/core/pod/storage/storage.go:66) uses a generic store that applies the podStrategy. The strategy's PrepareForCreate method (pkg/registry/core/pod/strategy.go:86) initializes the pod status to PodPending and performs validation before the pod is persisted to etcd.\n\nThe complete flow is: Deployment spec change → DeploymentController.syncDeployment → rolloutRolling → getNewReplicaSet (creates ReplicaSet) → ReplicaSetController.syncReplicaSet → manageReplicas → RealPodControl.CreatePods → createPods (API call) → Pod REST storage → podStrategy.PrepareForCreate → Pod persisted to etcd."
